"487","<BODY STYLE=font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif>"
"488","<P STYLE=margin: 0></P>"
"489","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 0.7in 12pt 0; text-align: center><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif><B>Report"
"490","of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm</B></FONT></P>"
"491","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>To the Board"
"492","of Trustees and Shareholders of American Funds Short-Term Tax-Exempt Bond Fund, Limited Term Tax-Exempt Bond Fund of America,"
"493","The Tax-Exempt Bond Fund of America, American High-Income Municipal Bond Fund and American Funds Tax-Exempt Fund of New York</FONT></P>"
"494","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"495","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>In planning"
"496","and performing our audits of the financial statements of American Funds Short-Term Tax-Exempt Bond Fund, Limited Term Tax-Exempt"
"497","Bond Fund of America, The Tax-Exempt Bond Fund of America, American High-Income Municipal Bond Fund and American Funds Tax-Exempt"
"498","Fund of New York (hereafter referred to as the &#8220;Funds&#8221;) as of and for the periods ended July 31, 2013, in accordance"
"499","with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Funds&#8217; internal control"
"500","over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for"
"501","the purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for"
"502","the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly,"
"503","we do not express an opinion on the effectiveness of the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting.</FONT></P>"
"504","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"505","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>The management"
"506","of the Funds is responsible for establishing and maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting. In fulfilling"
"507","this responsibility, estimates and judgments by management are required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of controls."
"508","A fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability"
"509","of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted"
"510","accounting principles. A fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1)"
"511","pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions"
"512","of the assets of the funds; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation"
"513","of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the"
"514","funds are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and trustees of the funds; and (3) provide reasonable"
"515","assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of a fund&#8217;s assets that"
"516","could have a material effect on the financial statements.</FONT></P>"
"517","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"518","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>Because of"
"519","its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections"
"520","of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes"
"521","in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.</FONT></P>"
"522","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"523","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>A deficiency"
"524","in internal control over financial reporting exists when the design or operation of a control does not allow management or employees,"
"525","in the normal course of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material"
"526","weakness is a deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a"
"527","reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the Funds&#8217; annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented"
"528","or detected on a timely basis.</FONT></P>"
"529","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"530","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>Our consideration"
"531","of the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting was for the limited purpose described in the first paragraph and"
"532","would not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal control over financial reporting that might be material weaknesses"
"533","under standards established by the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). However, we noted no deficiencies"
"534","in the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting and its operation, including controls over safeguarding securities,"
"535","that we consider to be material weaknesses as defined above as of July 31, 2013.</FONT></P>"
"536","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>&nbsp;</FONT></P>"
"537","<P STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0><FONT STYLE=font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif>This report"
"538","is intended solely for the information and use of management and the Board of Trustees of American Funds Short-Term Tax-Exempt"
"539","Bond Fund, Limited Term Tax-Exempt Bond Fund of America, The Tax-Exempt Bond Fund of America, American High-Income Municipal Bond"
"540","Fund and American Funds Tax-Exempt Fund of New York and the Securities and Exchange Commission and is not intended to be and should"
